reviews.review_text: special show I don't really feel that I have the right to be the first to review any show I didn't attend, but this one is a favorite.  I'm also a big fan of audience recordings.  It's great to hear another perspective from the board and some of the "acoustic reason" this show "went down" like it did.  "How sweet it is!"

Tied for 1st-Summer 77 with Cornell Always loved this 2nd set.  It pretty much has the best Estimated => Eyes you will ever hear.
The 'Ship of Fools' is my favorite as well. A very laid-back St. Stephen into the 1st ever '
Iko-Iko, then segues into a monster 'Not Fade Away', where Jerry turns up and sort of goes into very spacey 'dark-star-like leads' and then it rolls into 'Sugar Magnolia'. The segue into Sugar Magnolia is like they are playing at least 2 different songs at once. I have had this tape since 1984 and made it for all of my DH friends. This was our favorite tape.  Unfortunately, this show does not get the recognition it truly deserves. NOt saying it is better than 5-8, just an equally stellar alternative. I never get tired of it. Check it out. The 2nd Set.
